						<summary>

						<p>On a rock near the pond close to the Rāmaliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 155[5], <hi rend="italic">Māgha,</hi> ba. 5, corresponding to 1634 A.D. February 8.</p>						

						<p>Records the grant of some <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> land for maintaining a perpetual lamp in the temple of Kēśava at Maṇḍagiri by Chennaya, grandson of Vināyaka[llaya].</p>						

